The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 24 June is 43,585 (5,044.7 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 19 June, there were 494 new confirmed cases (57.2 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 12 June, there were 288 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 72% (206 extra cases).
